        {"body":"Cleveland Indians pitcher JOSE MESA went on national television in the Dominican Republic to tell his countrymen that he is innocent of a felony charge of sexual harassment. ''I want to tell the Dominican people that I am a man of irreproachable conduct and, as a public figure who has succeeded in the United States, they want to sully my", "date":"19961231", "title":"Mesa Proclaims Innocence", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/sports/mesa-proclaims-innocence.html"},
        {"body":"A day after North Korea expressed regret for sending a submarine into the South, the Clinton Administration announced today that North Korea had agreed for the first time to talk with South Korea and the United States about the possibility of negotiating a formal end to the Korean War. The agreement represented a significant breakthrough in efforts", "byline":"By STEVEN LEE MYERS", "date":"19961231", "title":"U.S. REPORTS FOES IN KOREA WILLING TO DISCUSS PEACE", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/world/us-reports-foes-in-korea-willing-to-discuss-peace.html"},
        {"body":"To the Editor: It is a tribute to Anthony Lewis's discernment that in the midst of the Hebron cliffhanger, he perceives the threat to Israel from religious extremism (column, Dec. 26). Many Israelis believe that once accommodation with the Palestinians is reached, the struggle for Israel's soul between militant ultra-orthodoxy and the proponents of", "date":"19961231", "title":"A Nation's Soul", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/opinion/l-a-nation-s-soul-972223.html"},
        {"body":"To the Editor: In your Dec. 26 editorial on French-American relations (''The Irascible Mr. Chirac''), you write that the United States has refused to turn over NATO's southern command to a French officer, something that France has never requested. France does want the two regional European commands assigned to European officers on a rotating basis.", "date":"19961231", "title":"U.S.-French Relations: A History of Cooperation", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/opinion/l-us-french-relations-a-history-of-cooperation-960659.html"},
        {"body":"When neighbors came to Mullah Mohammed Omar in the spring of 1994, they had a story that was shocking even by the grim standards of Afghanistan's 18-year-old civil war. Two teen-age girls from the mullah's village of Singesar had been abducted by one of the gangs of mujahedeen, or ''holy warriors,'' who controlled much of the Afghan countryside.", "byline":"By JOHN F. BURNS with STEVE LeVINE", "date":"19961231", "title":"How Afghans' Stern Rulers Took Hold", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/world/how-afghans-stern-rulers-took-hold.html"},
        {"body":"Russian troops will complete their withdrawal from Chechnya before elections in the province Jan. 27, Russian news agencies quoted officials as saying today. But officials made conflicting statements on when exactly the withdrawal, which is a part of a peace deal struck with Chechen rebels, could be completed. Itar-Tass quoted the chief of staff of", "date":"19961231", "title":"Russian Troops to Leave Chechnya in January", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/world/russian-troops-to-leave-chechnya-in-january.html"},
        {"body":"In a sign of improving relations on the Korean Peninsula, the Government here today handed over to North Korea the remains of 24 infiltrators who were killed after they slipped ashore from a North Korean submarine in September. The return of the remains marked a quick reward to North Korea for having issued a landmark statement of ''deep regret'' a", "byline":"By NICHOLAS D. KRISTOF", "date":"19961231", "title":"South Returns Remains", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/world/south-returns-remains.html"},
        {"body":"A front-page picture caption yesterday about the signing of a peace agreement in Guatemala located President Alvaro Arzu Irigoyen incorrectly in some copies. He was at the left, holding a peace torch with a guerrilla leader, not third from left.", "date":"19961231", "title":"Corrections", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/nyregion/c-corrections-971863.html"},
        {"body":"To the Editor: While Anthony Lewis is correct that the lack of harmony between the secular and religious sectors of Israeli society is dangerous (column, Dec. 26), there are valid reasons to dissent on issues he raises. Rather than pursue a policy of harmony, the stronger secular sector may have provoked conflicts it expected to win in order to", "date":"19961231", "title":"Jerusalem Thoroughfare Is Designed to Provoke", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/31/opinion/l-jerusalem-thoroughfare-is-designed-to-provoke-972215.html"},
        {"body":"After 36 years of civil war that left more than 100,000 people dead and devastated this country's society, a grateful but weary Guatemala formally returned to a state of peace today with the signing of a final armistice between the Government and the leftist guerrillas who have been its traditional adversaries. As thousands of people watched on", "byline":"By LARRY ROHTER", "date":"19961230", "title":"Guatemalans Formally End 36-Year Civil War, Central America's Longest and Deadliest", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1996/12/30/world/guatemalans-formally-end-36-year-civil-war-central-america-s-longest-deadliest.html"}
