        {"body":"Alexandra Chernikova did not want to move her family into a housing project, fearing it would be unclean and unsafe. So after she and her husband separated in 1996, she worked two jobs, hoping to make enough money to stay in their apartment in Brighton Beach, Brooklyn. But she could not afford the rent, and she and her son and daughter moved into", "byline":"By ADAM GERSHENSON", "date":"19981231", "title":"THE NEEDIEST CASES; Forceful Entry by Police Shatters Peace of Mind", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/31/nyregion/the-neediest-cases-forceful-entry-by-police-shatters-peace-of-mind.html"},
        {"body":"EUROPE RUSSIA: YELTSIN ATTACKS EXTREMISM -- President Boris N. Yeltsin ordered the Government to fight political and religious extremism in the wake of several recent anti-Semitic outbursts by Russian politicians. Mr. Yeltsin told Prime Minister Yevgeny M. Primakov and other senior officials to draw up a program to oppose extremism, the President's", "byline":"Compiled by Christopher S. Wren", "date":"19981231", "title":"World Briefing", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/31/world/world-briefing.html"},
        {"body":"When the man named Sor saw that he had been recognized, he covered his face with a scarf and tried to disappear into the crowd. But Vann Nath caught him. ''I held him by the arm and I asked him: 'Is it you? Is it you named Sor?' '' Mr. Vann Nath said, calling the man by his revolutionary nickname. ''He said, 'No, it's not me, you're confused.' But", "byline":"By SETH MYDANS", "date":"19981231", "title":"A MILLION GHOSTS: A special report.; Revenge or Justice? Cambodians Confront the Past", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/31/world/million-ghosts-special-report-revenge-justice-cambodians-confront-past.html"},
        {"body":"SATOW-Jed. On December 29, 1998. Beloved son of Phillip and Donna Satow. Loving brother of Michael and Julie, and sister-inlaw Barbara. Dear uncle of Max. Cherished grandson of Shirley Pechter & Sarah Satow. Services Thursday, 11:30 A.M., at Frank E. Campbell, 1076 Madison Avenue at 81st Street. SATOW-Jed. The Columbia College Alumni Association", "date":"19981231", "title":"Paid Notice: Deaths SATOW, JED", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/31/classified/paid-notice-deaths-satow-jed.html"},
        {"body":"President Alvaro Arzu has appealed for national reconciliation and asked Guatemalans to forgive the state for its role in the deaths and deprivation they suffered in 36 years of civil war. ''In the name of the state, I ask forgiveness,'' Mr. Arzu said on Tuesday at a ceremony marking the second anniversary of the signing of a United", "date":"19981231", "title":"Apology to Guatemalans", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/31/world/apology-to-guatemalans.html"},
        {"body":"Israelis joke that theirs is a country of six million people, six million cell phones and now, six million candidates for Prime Minister. Every time Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu turns around, he faces a potential new rival, not from the left but from his own conservative camp -- and, as of today, from his own Cabinet, after Environment", "byline":"By DEBORAH SONTAG", "date":"19981231", "title":"Netanyahu Challenged From Left And Right", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/31/world/netanyahu-challenged-from-left-and-right.html"},
        {"body":"The powder keg in the small New Hampshire town has a name: Wade Whitehouse, keeper of the peace. As played with fierce, anguished intensity by Nick Nolte, who gives the performance of his career in Paul Schrader's quietly stunning new film, Wade works part time as Lawford's policeman and knows that his hardest job is policing himself. But during", "byline":"By JANET MASLIN", "date":"19981230", "title":"FILM REVIEW; A Suppressed Son Erupts With Molten Emotions", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/30/movies/film-review-a-suppressed-son-erupts-with-molten-emotions.html"},
        {"body":"''Je suis low bat.'' Whenever ''low bat'' starts flashing on their cellular phones, people here know that their batteries are nearly drained. The phrase is a fashionable one here in the capital's deluxe hotels and gated villas, a coinage peculiar to a place where regular phones don't work and only the thin upper layer of society can afford", "byline":"By NORIMITSU ONISHI", "date":"19981230", "title":"Long War Saps Spirit And Money In Congo", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/30/world/long-war-saps-spirit-and-money-in-congo.html"},
        {"body":"People thought nothing could top Joel Grey's portrayal of the seedy, seductive M.C. in ''Cabaret.'' Then they saw Alan Cumming in the role (in this year's Roundabout Theater revival). So until now, a lot of people thought nothing could top Mr. Cumming. Tonight there is opportunity for direct comparison, and synergy, when the two men sing and gyrate", "byline":"By ANITA GATES", "date":"19981230", "title":"TELEVISION REVIEW; From the Kit Kat to the Lollipop", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/30/arts/television-review-from-the-kit-kat-to-the-lollipop.html"},
        {"body":"Iris Murdoch, the celebrated author of 26 rigorously intellectual novels, stood uncertainly in the doorway of her living room, her face frozen in the blank expression that is a sure badge of Alzheimer's disease. It was only when she saw her husband, the critic, professor and novelist John Bayley, that a flicker of comprehension sparked in her eyes.", "byline":"By SARAH LYALL", "date":"19981230", "title":"ARTS ABROAD: Devotion Refuses to Yield; Alzheimer's Disease Cannot Divide a Literary Couple", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/12/30/books/arts-abroad-devotion-refuses-yield-alzheimer-s-disease-cannot-divide-literary.html"}
